-- Singapore stock market opens up 0.3 pct after delay 
-- By Aradhana Aravindan
-- Tue Dec 02, 2014 11:36PM EST
-- None



SINGAPORE, Dec 3 (Reuters) - Singapore's stock market opened up 0.3 percent on Wednesday after the bourse operator, Singapore Exchange Ltd (SGX) <SGXL.SI>, delayed the start of trading in securities due to a software defect.

At 12:32 p.m. (0432 GMT), the Straits Times Index <.FTSTI> was 0.27 percent higher at 3,331.57.